General.Name: KickCoin
General.Description:
KickCoin is a cryptocurrency that will be accepted and used by the projects that are launched on the KICKICO platform (as well as by all its partners). KICK will be primarily used as a payment method on the platform. KICKICO takes half the commission (4%) of ICO campaigns launched in their tokens to the KICKONOMY fund.

KickCoin can't be mined by users and are instead emitted during the fundraising process - whenever somebody contributes to the campaign directly to the smart contract address, new KickCoins are minted and sent to the address, from which the payment in ETH was made.

ICO Details:

KICKICO will be holding its ICO on August 29, 2017. The ICO token supply represents 75,4% (73,6 ICO, 1,8% - preICO) of the total token supply, so there will be a total of 815000000 tokens available, for 0.0003333 each at the offering. The ICO funding target is 70,000 ETH, the funding cap is 200,000 ETH and is expected to end on September 16, 2017or when the funding cap is reached.

KICKICO crowdsale campaign will feature a bonus structure and bounties.

Token Reserve Split (24.6%):

  • 12.3% Founders;
  • 12.3% Bounties, Advisory, Lottery, Seed investors, PR Pools;

Bonus Structure:

  • 66.67% Bonus (1 ETH = 6000 KC); - PreICO;
  • 33.33% Bonus (1 ETH = 3000 KC); - ICO;
  • 00,00% Bonus (1 ETH = 2000 KC); - Launch;
